# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the code is
#   intended to run in multiple environments; otherwise, check them in:
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if you want to keep dependency versions locked,
#   you should share Pipfile.lock with your team.
#   In that case, you should not ignore it:
# Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, poetry.lock contains exact versions of dependency.
#   You should commit poetry.lock to version control.
# poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pdm.lock contains exact versions of dependency.
# pdm.lock

# runtime package share
#   Similar to Pipfile.lock, pixi.lock contains exact versions of dependency.
# pixi.lock

# PEP 582; project local packages (this directory should be empty)
